  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The U.S. accepts a limited number of refugees each year, setting record-low admission caps these past few years. Trump slashed refugee admissions by over 85% and it will take years to repair this damage. Help the IRC deliver critical assistance to families in the U.S. who have fled war or persecution, including: education, livelihoods training, youth programs, and citizenship assistance to refugees and other vulnerable immigrant populations.</narrative>
